Pizza with Mac & Cheese (Pizza with Macaroni & Cheese)

Ingredients:

* 1 pound ground beef (best if you use 80/20)*
* 1/4 cup chopped onion
* 2 cloves garlic, minced
* 1 tablespoon uncooked elbow macaroni noodles
* 1 can of drained canned tomato (diced)
* Sauce - mix of tomato, olive oil, minced garlic (prepared from dipping jar, pizza sauce, or crushed red pepper, etc., to taste)
* Cheeses - shredded or grated mozzarella and cheddar (other cheeses may also be sprinkled on, just be aware of the cooking process and taste)

Instructions:

cooking pizzas. Whether you're using a pizza stove, a pizza stone, or regular oven racks, preheat according to the pizza stone or oven method.
2. In a large bowl, combine ground beef, chopped onion and minced garlic for a few minutes until the meat is cooked. *You can stop here and make regular beef pizza if you prefer not to make Mac and Cheese Pizza.
3. Add the drained canned tomatoes to the ground beef and mix well. Add the Macaroni noodles to the mixture and cook until the noodles are coated in the seasoned mixture.
4. Transform the pizza into a Mac & Cheese pizza. Place the mozzarella cheese over the crumbled beef and macaroni mixture. Finely. Ignore the chopped noodle pieces - they'll be more substantial than regulation noodle widths, helping keep the mixture compact.
5. Periodically toss the pizza (watch out for the broken noodles) into a saucing mixture or use a pizza sauce (check the recipe for the best sauce, maybe a spicy one, as tomato chunks aren't visually intuitive on this pizza).
6. Sprinkle shredded or grated cheese (such as cheddar) over the noodle mixture.
